name: Sea World San Diego
description: Sea World San Diego is an animal theme park, oceanarium, outside aquarium, and marine mammal park, located in San Diego, California, United States. The park is owned by SeaWorld Entertainment.
address: Mission Bay Park, 500 Sea World Dr, San Diego, CA 92109

name: Legoland
description: Legoland California is a theme park, miniature park, and aquarium located in Carlsbad, California, based on the Lego toy brand.

name: UCSD
description: The University of California, San Diego is a public research university located in the La Jolla  neighborhood of San Diego, California, in the United States.

name: SDSU
description: San Diego State University is a public research university in San Diego, California, and is the largest and oldest higher education institution in San Diego County.

name: USD
description: The University of San Diego is a private Roman Catholic university in San Diego, California, United States. The university offers 42 baccalaureate degrees, and several degrees in law, nursing, and other doctorate programs.

name: San Diego City College
description: San Diego City College is a public, two-year community college located in San Diego,California. City College is part of the San Diego Community College District along with San Diego Mesa College

name: National University
description: National University is a private, nonprofit institution of higher education in California. Founded in 1971, National University is headquartered in La Jolla, California, United States.

name: San Diego Mesa College
description: San Diego Mesa College is a public, two year community college located in the community of Clairemont Mesa in the City of San Diego, California in the United States.
address: 7250 Mesa College Dr, San Diego, CA 92111

name: Ashford University
description: Ashford University is an online for-profit university headquartered in San Diego, California. It is the largest educational holding of Bridgepoint Education.
address: 8620 Spectrum Center Blvd, San Diego, CA 92123

name: Point Loma Nazarene University
description: Point Loma Nazarene University is a Christian liberal arts college. Its main campus is located on the Point Loma oceanfront in San Diego, California, United States. It was founded in 1902 as a Bible college by the Church of the Nazarene.

name: Cabrillo National Monument
description: Cabrillo National Monument is at the southern tip of the Point Loma Peninsula in San Diego, California. It commemorates the landing of Juan Rodríguez Cabrillo at San Diego Bay on September 28, 1542.
address: 1800 Cabrillo Memorial Dr, San Diego, CA 92106

name: Fort Rosecrans Cemetery
description: Fort Rosecrans National Cemetery is a federal military cemetery in the city of San Diego, California.
address: 1800 Cabrillo Memorial Dr, San Diego, CA 92106

name: Mount Soledad
description: Mount Soledad is a prominent landmark in the city of San Diego, California, United States. The mountaintop is the site of the Mount Soledad cross

name: Coronado Bridge
description: The San Diego–Coronado Bridge, locally referred to as the Coronado Bridge, is a prestressed concrete/steel girder bridge, crossing over San Diego Bay in the United States, linking San Diego with Coronado, California.

name: Point Loma Lighthouse
description: The original Point Loma Lighthouse is a historic lighthouse located on the Point Loma peninsula at the mouth of San Diego Bay
address: NSC San Diego, Point Loma Annex, 1800 Cabrillo Memorial Dr, San Diego, CA 92106

name: Embracing Peace Statue
description: If the photograph of raising the American flag on Iwo Jima is the quintessential World War II icon for triumph in a just war, then 'Unconditional Surrender' is the icon for the just rewards of victory.

name: Torrey Pines Gliderport
description: The Torrey Pines Gliderport is a city-owned private-use glider airport located in La Jolla
address: 2800 Torrey Pines Scenic Dr, La Jolla, CA 92037

name: Mormon Battalion Historic Site
description: This newly remodeled center evokes Old San Diego and includes hands-on exhibits and resources for learning more about those who served in the Battalion.

name: Mission Basilica San Diego de Alcala
description: Visitors can explore the grounds of this 18th-century, still-active mission, the state's first.
address: 10818 San Diego Mission Rd, San Diego, CA 92108

name: National Salute to Bob Hope and the Military
description: On the plaza, there are 15 life-sized bronze statues, arranged as if attending a Bob Hope show. Each figure represents a serviceman from a different conflict.

name: San Diego California Temple
description: The San Diego California Temple is the 47th constructed and 45th operating temple of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.

name: Salk Institute for Biological Studies
description: The Salk Institute for Biological Studies is an independent, non-profit, scientific research institute located in La Jolla, San Diego, California, United States.
address: 10010 N Torrey Pines Rd, La Jolla, CA 92037

name: Balboa park
description: Located in San Diego, Balboa park is where nature and culture meet. There are more than 17 mueseums filled with everything from dinosaurs to space travels.

name: Old Town San Diego State Historic Park
description: Old Town San Diego State Historic Park, located in the Old Town neighborhood of San Diego, California, is a state protected historical park in San Diego

name: Torrey Pines State Natural Reserve
description: Torrey Pines State Natural Reserve is 2,000 acres of coastal state park located in the community of La Jolla, in San Diego, California, off North Torrey Pines Road.
address: 12600 N Torrey Pines Rd, La Jolla, CA 92037

name: Casa de Estudillo
description: The Casa de Estudillo, also known as the Estudillo House, is a historic adobe house in San Diego, California, United States.

name: Santa Fe Depot
description: The Santa Fe Depot in San Diego, California, USA, is a union station built by the Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway to replace the small Victorian-style structure erected in 1887 for the California Southern Railroad Company.

name: Balboa Theatre
description: The Balboa Theatre is a historic vaudeville/movie theatre in downtown San Diego, built in 1924. Listed on the National Register of Historic Places, the Balboa was refurbished and reopened as a performing arts venue in 2008.

name: La Jolla Woman's Club
description: The La Jolla Woman's Club is a historic building in La Jolla, a neighborhood of San Diego, California.

name: Mission Trails Regional Park
description: Mission Trails Regional Park is a 5,800-acre open space preserve within the city of San Diego, California, established in 1974. It is the sixth-largest municipally owned park in the United States, and the largest in California
address: 1 Father Junipero Serra Trail, San Diego, CA 92119

name: Los Penasquitos Trail Head
description: Los Penasquitos Trail is very nice and relaxing. Come and enjoy a lovely hike right here in San Diego
address: 300 Sorrento Valley Blvd, San Diego, CA 92121

name: Tecolote Canyon Natural Park
description: This park running along the coast & up to the mouth of Tecolote Canyon includes a visitors center.

name: Los Peñasquitos Canyon Preserve
description: Los Peñasquitos Canyon Preserve is an urban park in San Diego, California. Stretching approximately 7 miles, the park encompasses some 4,000 acres of both Peñasquitos and Lopez canyons, and is one of the largest urban parks in the United States
address: 12020 Black Mountain Rd, San Diego, CA 92129

name: San Diego-La Jolla Underwater Park
description: The San Diego-La Jolla Underwater Park spans 6,000 acres of ocean bottom and tidelands. The park's four distinct habitats make it a popular destination for snorkelers and scuba divers.
address: 8302 Camino Del Oro, La Jolla, CA 92037

name: Fanuel Street Park
description: Great place for families to visit

name: Sunset Cliffs Natural Park
description: Natural cliffs overlooking the Pacific Ocean offer views of the coast & the occasional cliff diver.

name: Presidio Park
description: Presidio Park is a city historic park in San Diego, California. It is the site where the San Diego Presidio and the San Diego Mission, the first European settlements in what is now the western United States, were founded in 1769

name: Waterfront Park
description: Public park featuring spray fountains, grassy areas & lots of play equipment for kids.

name: Mission Bay Park
description: Vast bayside spot popular for sand & surf sports, sunbathing, boats, picnics & dog-friendly beaches.
address: 2688 East Mission Bay Drive, San Diego, CA 92109

name: Shoreline Park
description: Mile-long scenic park offering a bayside promenade & fishing pier, plus picnic areas & public art.
address: 2200 Shelter Island Dr, San Diego, CA 92106

name: Whaley House
description: The Whaley House is an 1857 Greek Revival style residence, a California Historical Landmark, and museum located in Old Town, San Diego, California. It is currently maintained by Save Our Heritage Organisation
address: 2476 San Diego Ave, San Diego, CA 92110

name: George W. Marston House
description: The George W. Marston House, or George Marston House and Gardens, also referred to as the George and Anna Marston House or the Marston House, is a museum and historic landmark located in San Diego and maintained by Save Our Heritage Organisation.

name: Chicano Park
description: Chicano Park is a 32,000 square meter park located beneath the San Diego-Coronado Bridge in Barrio Logan, a predominantly Mexican American and Mexican-immigrant community in central San Diego, California.

name: Hotel del Coronado
description: Housed in a grand 1888 Victorian property on Coronado Island, this upscale beachside resort is a 10-minute drive from downtown San Diego.

name: Japanese Friendship Garden
description: The Japanese Friendship Garden, also known as San Kei En is a Japanese Garden within Balboa Park, San Diego
address: 215 Pan American Rd E, San Diego, CA 92101

name: Sea Port Village
description: Seaport Village is a waterfront shopping and dining complex adjacent to San Diego Bay in downtown San Diego, California. It is located at 849 West Harbor Drive, at the intersection of Harbor Drive and Kettner.
address: 849 W Harbor Dr, San Diego, CA 92101

name: Old Point Loma Lighthouse
description: The original Point Loma Lighthouse is a historic lighthouse located on the Point Loma peninsula at the mouth of San Diego Bay in San Diego, California. It is situated in the Cabrillo National Monument.
address: NSC San Diego, Point Loma Annex, 1800 Cabrillo Memorial Dr, San Diego, CA 92106
